- Collanus, M. and Heinonen, T. (2012). Arts making as an act of theory. In Art and Social Justice Education. Routledge, pp. 83-88.
- Fleetwood, N. R. (2019). Troubling vision: Performance, visuality, and blackness. University of Chicago Press.
- Foster, C. (2022). Local youth help create and unveil the" Sounds of our Soul" mural in downtown. UWIRE Text, 1-1.
- Kelley, R.D. (2020) Freedom dreams: The black radical imagination. Beacon Press.
- Sharpe, C. (2016). In the wake: On blackness and being. Duke University Press.
- Summers, B. (2022) Black insurgent aesthetics and the public imaginary. Urban Geography. 43(6): 837-847.


